{"model": "Qwen 2.5 7B Instruct", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "logic_ages__t3_cot", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 634.9, "generation_tps": 102.8, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 2.9, "output": "Let's denote Bob's current age as \\( B \\) and Alice's current age as \\( A \\).\n\nFrom the problem, we know:\n1. Alice is twice as old as Bob:\n\\[ A = 2B \\]\n\n2. In 10 years, Alice will be 1.5 times as old as Bob:\n\\[ A + 10 = 1.5 \\times (B + 10) \\]\n\nFirst, substitute \\( A = 2B \\) into the second equation:\n\\[ 2B + 10 = 1.5 \\times (B + 10) \\]\n\nNow, expand the right side:\n\\[ 2B + 10 = 1.5B + 15 \\]\n\nNext, isolate \\( B \\) by subtracting \\( 1.5B \\) from both sides:\n\\[ 2B - 1.5B + 10 = 15 \\]\n\\[ 0.5B + 10 = 15 \\]\n\nSubtract 10 from both sides:\n\\[ 0.5B = 5 \\]\n\nFinally, solve for \\( B \\) by dividing both sides by 0.5:\n\\[ B = \\frac{5}{0.5} \\]\n\\[ B = 10 \\]\n\nSo, Bob is currently 10 years old.\n\nANSWER: 10", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "a33ec0efd7f9"}
